      "side": 1,
      "message": "I still think that if the argument is a comma-separated list of tag specifications, that \"android_parse_debug_tags\" would be a better name for the method, and \"tags\" a better name for the argument.  These are more specific, in a useful way.  If --debug \u003cxxx\u003e were ever able to have an \u003cxxx\u003e that was something other than a tag list, then I would agree to call the union of tags and the new things \"options\", and have a method that could parse all such options.  But we don\u0027t have that yet.",
